<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871022-0101 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Horn andamp; Hardart Co.</HL><DD> 10/22/87</DD><SO>  </SO><IN> HORBUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Horn andamp; Hardart Co. said it has been in discussions with members of management and others about a possible leveraged buyout but that the talks are unlikely to result in an offer due to &quot;uncertainties&quot; in the financial markets.    The direct marketing and food-service concern, based in Las Vegas, Nev., also said it believes its shares currently are undervalued and plans to buy them on the open market. Barry W. Florescue, chairman and president, also plans to buy shares on the open market, the company added.    A spokesman said the company and Mr. Florescue may buy a total of as many as 1,750,000 shares, or 12% of the company's shares outstanding. </TEXT></DOC>